MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 2ed2c0874b1faeb4597781ccb833e1e8, type: 3}
  m_Name: DrAnglerDialogue
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCDialogue
  npcName: Dr. Angler
  npcPortrait: {fileID: 0}
  dialogueLines:
  - Greetings! My name is Dr. Angler. I heard you were sent by my colleague to assist
    me with my research.
  - Did my colleague tell you anything about the research we will be conducting?
  - "No? Perfect! A fresh pair of eyes! To start, I have a gift for you\u2014 this
    pocketwatch here. "
  - Hmm... you don't seem too pleased. Nonetheless, I can assure you that its mechanisms
    will shock you.
  - Have you ever used...
  - ...a time machine?!
  - Wow! I wish you saw the look on your face! I bet you didn't expect me to say
    that.
  - To be quite honest with you, it's still in the works; but nothing to worry about,
    all of my prototypes have adequately
  - transported mice... somewhere... they haven't returned yet, but I'm sure that's
    because they don't have fingers to use
  - the pocketwatch like you and I do. Goodness me, I am rambling on and on. Let
    me tell you about my research.
  - I am currently researching fish from the many different time periods that marine
    life has existed in.
  - "However, with this research comes some difficulty\u2014 there is no way for
    me to analyze their live behaviours. All I have"
  - are some fossils, which while useful, they really don't explain a lot of fish
    behaviours. This is where you come in!
  - I am entrusting you with the pocketwatch to retrieve the fish I need for my research
    from each time period. Isn't that fun?!
  - I know that sounds scary, with dinosaurs and all, but rest assured that there
    is nothing to worry about. Since the
  - pocketwatch is portable, if you find yourself in a difficult situation, you can
    just travel back to the present.
  - 'The only reason I cannot go is because, well, who will conduct and protect the
    research if I''m not here? Haha! '
  - We need to get started on the research as soon as possible. The museum is counting
    on us!
  - 'To open the pocketwatch, press E. Then, choose the time period and hit teleport.
    Take this device as well; it''s called the  '
  - Talkinator. No, it's not just a walkie talkie. It uses frequencies that allow
    us to communicate beyond the boundaries of
  - "space and time and\u2014 sorry, I'm rambling again. I will be able to speak
    with you using the Talkinator."
  - One last thing before you go! To record your findings, take this research logbook.
    You can open it with Q. Let me actually
  - record some information about the first fish for you to find. I don't know exactly
    where to find it, but I'll write what I know.
  - Okay, there you go. Good luck on your adventure. When you're done, come back
    to me!
  typingSpeed: 0.025
